\section{YAML}

\begin{note}
YAML stands for \emph{Yaml Ain't a Markup Language}.
Python does not have built-in support for YAML;
you need to pip install the \lstinline{PyYAML} package,
and then import the \lstinline{yaml} module.
You can find the full documentation of YAML at \url{https://yaml.org/}.
YAML is famously hated-on by the programmer community;
see for example \lstinline{https://noyaml.com/}.
\end{note}
